cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses discriminative feature learning and attention mechanisms, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves cross-domain adaptation, which can be related to information retrieval, so cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
